---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="deja — local-first agent memory"
  description="Cross-session memory for agents. Four verbs over SQLite + FTS5, exposed via a 3-tool MCP server. The next agent finds what the last one wrote."
>
  {/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      Hero — brain.jpg backdrop, wordmark, the primitive truth.
      ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
  <section class="pt-16 sm:pt-24 pb-14">
    <div
      class="relative border border-brass/20 rounded-sm p-8 sm:p-14 overflow-hidden bg-cover bg-center bg-no-repeat shadow-hero"
    >
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-cover bg-center bg-no-repeat -z-10 opacity-90"
        style="background-image: url('/brain.jpg');"
      ></div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-void/70 via-void/85 to-void/95 -z-10"></div>

      <div class="relative">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.28em] uppercase text-brass mb-5">
          local-first agent memory
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-serif-sc text-[3.5rem] sm:text-[5.5rem] leading-none font-bold tracking-tight m-0 mb-6">
          deja
        </h1>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-lg sm:text-xl text-chrome-dark max-w-[640px] mb-3 leading-relaxed">
          Cross-session memory for agents, backed by SQLite and FTS5. The next agent finds what the last one wrote, through a tiny 3-tool MCP server.
        </p>
        <p class="font-serif italic font-light text-[15px] text-brass-light/85 max-w-[640px] mb-10 leading-relaxed">
          deja gives agents memory. It doesn&rsquo;t force them to use it.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 items-center">
          <a
            href="#install"
            class="font-mono px-6 py-3.5 rounded-sm font-semibold text-[11px] tracking-[0.18em] uppercase border border-brass-dark bg-gradient-to-b from-steel-light to-steel text-chrome shadow-btn hover:-translate-y-px active:translate-y-px transition-transform"
          >
            Install
          </a>
          <a
            href="#verbs"
            class="font-mono px-6 py-3.5 rounded-sm font-semibold text-[11px] tracking-[0.18em] uppercase border border-brass/15 bg-transparent text-chrome-dark hover:bg-brass/5 hover:text-brass transition-colors"
          >
            See the verbs
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/acoyfellow/deja"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
            class="font-mono px-6 py-3.5 rounded-sm font-semibold text-[11px] tracking-[0.18em] uppercase border border-brass/15 bg-transparent text-chrome-dark hover:bg-brass/5 hover:text-brass transition-colors"
          >
            GitHub
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-x-8 gap-y-4 text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-chrome-dark/70">
          <div>
            <div class="text-brass-light text-[10px] mb-1">Storage</div>
            <div>SQLite + FTS5</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-brass-light text-[10px] mb-1">Surface</div>
            <div>3-tool MCP</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-brass-light text-[10px] mb-1">Tests</div>
            <div>28 / 28 green</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-brass-light text-[10px] mb-1">Recall@1 (fixture)</div>
            <div>100%</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      Four verbs — the centerpiece. Each verb gets a brass-bordered
      card with a description and a code snippet showing real usage.
      ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
  <section id="verbs" class="py-14 scroll-mt-24">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.28em] uppercase text-brass mb-3">
        the api
      </div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight m-0 mb-3">
        Four verbs in the library, three on MCP.
      </h2>
      <p class="font-serif font-light text-chrome-dark max-w-[680px] leading-relaxed">
        <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass">remember</code> drafts a slip.
        <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass">keep</code> promotes it.
        <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass">handoff</code> closes the session.
        <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass">recall</code> finds it from any process on the same DB.
      </p>
      <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/70 max-w-[680px] leading-relaxed mt-3">
        On MCP, <code class="font-mono text-[12px] text-brass">keep</code> is folded into <code class="font-mono text-[12px] text-brass">deja_remember</code> via the <code class="font-mono text-[12px] text-brass">keep:&nbsp;true</code> flag &mdash; one tool call, not two. Chain-shaped slips also auto-roll into the session handoff (see verbs below).
      </p>
    </div>

    {/* The flow diagram — animated mechanism */}
    <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-void-deep/60 px-6 py-2 mb-10 shadow-card">
      <div class="flow-container">
        <div class="flow-wire"></div>
        <div class="flow-node">
          <div class="flow-node-ring"><span class="flow-node-icon">jot</span></div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">remember</div>
          <div class="flow-node-desc">Draft a slip. Auto-expires in 24h.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-node">
          <div class="flow-node-ring"><span class="flow-node-icon">lock</span></div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">keep</div>
          <div class="flow-node-desc">Promote to permanent. Survives GC.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-node">
          <div class="flow-node-ring"><span class="flow-node-icon">end</span></div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">handoff</div>
          <div class="flow-node-desc">Close the session for the next agent.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-node">
          <div class="flow-node-ring"><span class="flow-node-icon">find</span></div>
          <div class="flow-node-label">recall</div>
          <div class="flow-node-desc">Find slips + the most recent handoff.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Verb cards */}
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
      {/* remember */}
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/40 shadow-card overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-brass/10 px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between bg-void-deep/50">
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass-light">d.remember(text, opts?)</code>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-chrome-dark/60">draft → kept</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-serif text-sm text-chrome-dark leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Drafts auto-expire in 24h unless promoted via
            <code class="font-mono text-[12px] text-brass">keep</code>.
          </p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-[12px] leading-relaxed text-chrome-dark bg-void-deep/80 border border-brass/10 rounded-sm p-3 overflow-x-auto shadow-code"><span class="text-brass-light">const</span> slip = d.<span class="text-brass">remember</span>(<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"the user prefers vitest over jest"</span>);
<span class="text-brass-light">const</span> wip   = d.<span class="text-brass">remember</span>(<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"mid-refactor of auth.ts"</span>, &#123;
  tags: [<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"wip"</span>, <span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"refactor"</span>],
&#125;);</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* keep */}
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/40 shadow-card overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-brass/10 px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between bg-void-deep/50">
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass-light">d.keep(ids)</code>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-chrome-dark/60">auto-rolls handoffs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-serif text-sm text-chrome-dark leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Promote drafts. If the slip is chain-shaped &mdash; a decision, preference, wip
            note &mdash; deja also writes a session handoff so the next agent finds it on
            <em>any</em> recall.
          </p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-[12px] leading-relaxed text-chrome-dark bg-void-deep/80 border border-brass/10 rounded-sm p-3 overflow-x-auto shadow-code"><span class="text-brass-light">const</span> dec = d.<span class="text-brass">remember</span>(<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"Decision: use bun:sqlite, not better-sqlite3."</span>);
d.<span class="text-brass">keep</span>([dec.id]);
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// also writes a session handoff that mentions the decision</span></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* handoff */}
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/40 shadow-card overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-brass/10 px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between bg-void-deep/50">
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass-light">d.handoff(&#123; summary, next? &#125;)</code>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-chrome-dark/60">one per session</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-serif text-sm text-chrome-dark leading-relaxed mb-4">
            End-of-session note in your own voice. Surfaced at the top of every recall on
            this DB &mdash; the canonical &ldquo;pick up where we left off&rdquo; primitive.
          </p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-[12px] leading-relaxed text-chrome-dark bg-void-deep/80 border border-brass/10 rounded-sm p-3 overflow-x-auto shadow-code">d.<span class="text-brass">handoff</span>(&#123;
  summary: <span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"shipped the auth refactor"</span>,
  next: [<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"wire it into the gateway"</span>],
&#125;);</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* recall */}
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/40 shadow-card overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-brass/10 px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between bg-void-deep/50">
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-brass-light">d.recall(query)</code>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-chrome-dark/60">trust labels</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-serif text-sm text-chrome-dark leading-relaxed mb-4">
            FTS5 over kept + draft slips, returned with trust labels
            (<code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">high</code> /
            <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">medium</code> /
            <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">low</code>). Falls back to the latest
            cross-session handoff when the current session has none.
          </p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-[12px] leading-relaxed text-chrome-dark bg-void-deep/80 border border-brass/10 rounded-sm p-3 overflow-x-auto shadow-code"><span class="text-brass-light">const</span> r = d.<span class="text-brass">recall</span>(<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"test runner"</span>);
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// r.hits[0].slip.text === "the user prefers vitest over jest"</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// r.activeHandoff.summary === "shipped the auth refactor"</span></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      Chain section — the headline result of the cross-session test.
      Two columns: writer code + reader code, side by side.
      ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
  <section id="chain" class="py-14 scroll-mt-24">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.28em] uppercase text-brass mb-3">
        the chain
      </div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight m-0 mb-3">
        Writer hands off. Reader picks up.
      </h2>
      <p class="font-serif font-light text-chrome-dark max-w-[680px] leading-relaxed">
        Two agents, same SQLite file, separate processes. The reader recalls the
        previous handoff on its first turn.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
      {/* Writer */}
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 shadow-card overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-brass/10 px-5 py-3 bg-void-deep/50 flex items-center justify-between">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-brass glow-brass"></span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light">session A · writer</span>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-chrome-dark/60">monday 4pm</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-serif text-sm text-chrome-dark leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Mid-refactor. Stops at line 142, hands off, ends the session.
          </p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-[12px] leading-relaxed text-chrome-dark bg-void-deep/80 border border-brass/10 rounded-sm p-3 overflow-x-auto shadow-code">deja_handoff(&#123;
  summary: <span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"mid-refactor of auth.ts. stopped at line</span>
<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">  142 in parseToken(). next: migrate the JWT</span>
<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">  helper to lib/jwt.ts. tests will fail until</span>
<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">  the move is complete."</span>,
  next: [
    <span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"finish moving JWT helper from auth.ts:142"</span>,
    <span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"update imports in auth.ts"</span>,
    <span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"run test suite — should go from 4 failing to 0"</span>,
  ],
&#125;);</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Reader */}
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 shadow-card overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-brass/10 px-5 py-3 bg-void-deep/50 flex items-center justify-between">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-brass glow-brass"></span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light">session B · reader</span>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-chrome-dark/60">tuesday 9am</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-serif text-sm text-chrome-dark leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Fresh process. User says &ldquo;pick up where we left off.&rdquo;
          </p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-[12px] leading-relaxed text-chrome-dark bg-void-deep/80 border border-brass/10 rounded-sm p-3 overflow-x-auto shadow-code">deja_recall(<span class="text-[#9ece6a]">"current work"</span>);

<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// → # previous handoff</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// →   mid-refactor of auth.ts. stopped at</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// →   line 142 in parseToken()...</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// →</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// → next:</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// →   - finish moving JWT helper</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// →   - update imports</span>
<span class="text-chrome-dark/60">// →   - run test suite</span></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="font-serif font-light text-chrome-dark/80 text-sm mt-6 max-w-[680px] leading-relaxed">
      Measured in benchmark loop 4 c3: the reader read the file, made the edit, ran
      the test suite, and reported back &mdash; using only the handoff as input.
      <a href="https://github.com/acoyfellow/deja/blob/main/docs/loops/2026-04-25-loop-4-cross-session-chain.md" class="text-brass hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Full transcript &rarr;</a>
    </p>

    {/* Where this fails — the boundary, named honestly. */}
    <div class="mt-10 border border-brass/10 rounded-sm bg-void-deep/40 px-5 py-4">
      <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light mb-2">where this fails</div>
      <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/85 leading-relaxed">
        If the question reads as world knowledge to the agent (&ldquo;how do you pronounce X?&rdquo;,
        &ldquo;what is pi to 10 digits?&rdquo;), the agent answers from training data and never queries
        memory &mdash; even when memory has the user&rsquo;s actual answer recorded. We measured this:
        <a href="https://github.com/acoyfellow/deja/blob/main/docs/loops/2026-04-25-loop-3-three-meta-tools.md" class="text-brass hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">loop 3 s8</a>
        and
        <a href="https://github.com/acoyfellow/deja/blob/main/docs/loops/2026-04-25-loop-4-cross-session-chain.md" class="text-brass hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">loop 4 c1</a>.
        It&rsquo;s a model-prior boundary, not a deja fix.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      Spec sheet — the honest "what's actually in the box".
      ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <div class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.28em] uppercase text-brass mb-3">
        what's in the box
      </div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight m-0 mb-3">
        ~600 lines of TypeScript.
      </h2>
      <p class="font-serif font-light text-chrome-dark max-w-[680px] leading-relaxed">
        Open the SQLite file with any client. The MCP server is a stdio process. Tool
        descriptions tell agents how to use them &mdash; no SKILL.md, no AGENTS.md.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 p-5 shadow-card">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light mb-2">storage</div>
        <div class="font-serif text-base text-chrome mb-1">~/.deja/deja.db</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/80 leading-relaxed">
          SQLite with WAL. Three tables: <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">slips</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">links</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">handoffs</code>. FTS5 virtual table
          with porter stemming over slip text and tags.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 p-5 shadow-card">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light mb-2">lifecycle</div>
        <div class="font-serif text-base text-chrome mb-1">draft → kept → expired</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/80 leading-relaxed">
          Append-only. State transitions update timestamps; text is never edited in place.
          Drafts auto-GC at 24h. Contradictions become new slips that link to the old.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 p-5 shadow-card">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light mb-2">ids</div>
        <div class="font-serif text-base text-chrome mb-1">ULID</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/80 leading-relaxed">
          26-character Crockford base32. Sortable by creation time. No external dependency.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 p-5 shadow-card">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light mb-2">surface</div>
        <div class="font-serif text-base text-chrome mb-1">3-tool MCP</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/80 leading-relaxed">
          <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">deja_recall</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">deja_remember</code>,
          <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">deja_handoff</code>.
          Tool descriptions and responses are the spec &mdash; no SKILL.md, no AGENTS.md.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 p-5 shadow-card">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light mb-2">trust labels</div>
        <div class="font-serif text-base text-chrome mb-1">high · medium · low</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/80 leading-relaxed">
          BM25 scores bucketed for the agent. Recall responses lead with
          <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">[high — recorded]</code> for
          decisive matches and tell the agent to verify
          <code class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass">[low]</code> ones.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-brass/15 rounded-sm bg-steel/30 p-5 shadow-card">
        <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-brass-light mb-2">runtime</div>
        <div class="font-serif text-base text-chrome mb-1">stdio process</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/80 leading-relaxed">
          No daemon, no network calls, no background service. The MCP server is launched
          on demand by the agent's MCP client.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      Limits — what deja isn't. Stated up front so people stop
      asking. Honest negative space is more credible than puffery.
      ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <div class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.28em] uppercase text-brass mb-3">
        limits
      </div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight m-0 mb-3">
        What deja isn't.
      </h2>
      <p class="font-serif font-light text-chrome-dark max-w-[680px] leading-relaxed">
        A focused tool that does one thing. Things it deliberately doesn't do:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
      <div class="border border-brass/10 rounded-sm bg-steel/20 px-4 py-3">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass-light tracking-[0.16em] uppercase mb-1">not a vector store</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/85 leading-relaxed">
          Lexical FTS5 only. Bring your own embeddings if you need semantic search.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-brass/10 rounded-sm bg-steel/20 px-4 py-3">
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] text-brass-light tracking-[0.16em] uppercase mb-1">not multi-user</div>
        <p class="font-serif font-light text-[13px] text-chrome-dark/85 leading-relaxed">
          One DB, one user. No accounts, no sharing, no permissions.
